slansky_doug@macmail1.cig.mot.com (Doug Slansky) writes:
> Having recently installed the new Apple System 7.5 and playing around 
> with the PowerTalk features, I was wondering what algorithim is used 
> for the signature/authentication function?

System 7.5 uses absolutely vanilla RSA PKCS/X.509 compliant digital 
signatures.

System 7.5 signer files contain a public key, encrypted private key, and owner 
certificate, all in X.509 format.


